# Auth: External IdP — TODO

The wizard scaffolded __DISPLAY_NAME__ with the external-IdP option, which is
intentionally a stub. You're expected to wire your own provider (Auth0, Clerk,
Keycloak, Cognito, your in-house SSO, etc.).

## What dashboard-kit did NOT do

- It did not pick an SDK or auth library — that's your call.
- It did not generate login/callback routes.
- The HTTP client at `src/api/client.js` (SPA) or your Inertia auth flow does NOT
  send any auth headers yet — replace the `__AUTH_INTERCEPTOR__` slot with your
  provider's token-fetch logic.

## Suggested checklist

1. Decide between OIDC (Authorization Code + PKCE for SPAs) or SAML.
2. Install your IdP's SDK and configure callback URLs.
3. On login success, store the access token (in memory if possible, sessionStorage
   if you must — avoid localStorage for sensitive tokens).
4. Add an axios interceptor that fetches a fresh token (your SDK usually handles
   refresh) and attaches `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.
5. On Laravel side, validate the JWT — `firebase/php-jwt` for raw OIDC, or use
   Sanctum + a custom guard if you want to keep the rest of the app conventional.
6. Update `routes/web.php` (Inertia) or `src/router.js` (SPA) to gate routes
   behind your auth check.

## Why we left this empty

The IdP integration is the most project-specific part of any auth system —
generating a half-baked Auth0 stub would just create work to undo. This file is
a checklist; replace it once you've made your choices.